    About The Park City Grand Plaza Kensington

    Occupying an imposing 19th century terrace house, The Park City Grand Plaza Kensington offers elegant and comfortable accommodation in London’s exclusive borough of Kensington & Chelsea. The stylishly appointed rooms are equipped with numerous up-to-date amenities such as plasma televisions, coffee makers, refrigerators, telephones and safes. Suites add separate living areas, whilst some upgraded rooms boast CD players and kitchenettes. All of the en-suites are air-conditioned and have free Wi-Fi access. Guests staying at The Park City Grand Plaza Kensington can relax in the elegant lounge or maintain their fitness routine at the on-site gym. Desktop computers and printers are available for guests to use at the business centre and there are also two meeting rooms on-site for those wishing to hold conferences or seminars. Popular Malaysian dishes are on offer at the Selesa Restaurant whilst an extensive selection of drinks is available at the bar. The Natural History Museum and Kensington Palace are both in close proximity to the hotel.

    About Travelodge London Central Aldgate East

    Located a little over a mile from Central London, the Travelodge London Central Aldgate East places guests near the Tower of London and Tower Hill tube station. The hotel offers flexible check-in and check-out options. The hotel offers single, double and family rooms, each one featuring a Sleepeezee bed, TV and desk. Tea and coffee making facilities are also provided. Guests are offered 30 minutes of free Wi-Fi access, after which extra charges apply. There is no on-site parking, although a paid public facility is available nearby. The hotel’s restaurant serves an unlimited breakfast buffet (free for kids), as well as providing options for lunch and late night dining. The hotel lies within two miles of Shakespeare’s Globe, within four miles of Buckingham Palace and the London Eye and within six miles of Regent’s Park and London Zoo.

    About Kimpton Fitzroy London

    Established in 1898, Kimpton Fitzroy London is a Grade II landmark building meticulously upgraded to meet modern standards without losing historical charm. It has a ballroom and eight other event spaces, plus overlooks Russell Square. Rooms at Kimpton Fitzroy London feature details like custom-designed carpeting and monogrammed pillows. They also provide free Wi-Fi and smart TVs. The mini fridge is stocked with free bottled water and milk, and the rooms have hot beverage-making supplies and sweet treats. In the bathrooms, guests will find complimentary luxury toiletries. This property has a 24-hour gym. Moreover, there is a concierge desk, plus a "corner shop" that sells conveniences and things guests may have left at home. Because this property has four dining options ranging from a coffeehouse to a seafood restaurant, travellers won't get hungry or thirsty. The hotel is a six-minute walk from the spectacular British Museum. Additionally, guests can reach the British Library and its millions of books via a 13-minute walk.

    About London Marriott Hotel Canary Wharf

    Situated a two-minute stroll from the Museum of London Docklands, London Marriott Hotel Canary Wharf offers an outstanding location by the water, plus 20 adaptable spaces for special events, including one that accommodates up to 300 guests. Rooms at London Marriott Hotel Canary Wharf feature LED TVs with international channels. Wi-Fi is also available. Guests also get coffee makers and minibars. The spacious desks help those with work to do, while the safes facilitate storing valuables. Some units have views of the quay. There is a 24-hour gym at this property, plus a sauna. Moreover, the West End is 25 minute away by public transport.

    About Sunborn London

    Docked majestically along one of the world’s most famous cities, the Sunborn London of London is a 124 metre floating hotel containing 136 spacious guestrooms, a day spa, restaurant and lounge bar. Each of the Sunborn London London’s 132 guestrooms and 4 suites contain en suite bathrooms, flat screen TVs, free Wi-Fi and touch-pad room controls. In addition to its event and meeting space, capable of hosting up to 250 guests, the hotel features the Elemis Spa, a perfect place for first-class pampering and a relaxing escape. In addition to 24-hour room service, the hotel’s Lands End Restaurant serves British fusion cuisine while its Sundown Bar provides guests an excellent place for a pre-dinner drink or nightcap. Sitting at the Royal Victoria Dock in the Docklands, the hotel is also moored next to the ExCel London convention centre, while being just a five minute stroll from the Docklands Light Rail.
